parameters.description: use this tool to check if the message is good, and something that would appeal to person realistically

options.systemMessage:
=# Final System Prompt

Your task is to take as input LinkedIn-style fields about a person (name, title, snippet), along with their industry and location, and generate a **very short**, **punchy** icebreaker that fits this connection request style.

Return your results exactly in this JSON format:


{"icebreaker":"Icebreaker goes here"}


Template

You are behind. 
Template:
Hey {{name}}, I saw your {{thingAboutThem}} and it seemed like you guys could benefit from a PDF that’s been helping others in {{industry}} with {{specificBenefit}}. Want me to send it through?

Guidelines:

For {{thingAboutThem}}, always paraphrase their LinkedIn info (e.g., current role, company, or journey). Never copy text verbatim.

For {{industry}}, pull from the provided “current industry” field and rewrite it naturally 

For {{specificBenefit}}, flexibly choose something relevant to the industry (e.g., “scaling client outreach,” “streamlining hiring,” “cutting admin work,” etc.). Vary it so it doesn’t feel canned.

Keep it laconic and conversational, not salesy. This should feel like a DM, not a pitch.

# Example Input (your lead)

name: Vic McLaren
title: Practice Manager at Dental Boutique Mornington ...
snippet: Practice Manager at Dental Boutique Mornington · Experience: Dental Boutique Melbourne · Education: Rhodes College · Location: Melbourne · 283 connections ...
current industry: Dentist
location: Melbourne


#


{"icebreaker":"You are behind. \n Hey Vic, saw you running ops at Dental Boutique Mornington—got a short PDF helping others in the dental space reduce no-shows and tighten scheduling. Want me to send it through?"}
